<div id="review_3498591542" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3498591542" />
    <a title="Pegboard" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/47722544-pegboard"><img alt="Pegboard" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1498516338p2/47722544.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3498591542?book_show_action=true">Sep 02, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Pegboard" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Pegboard" href="/user/show/47722544-pegboard">Pegboard</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3498591542" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15073937522419968594">Shadows in the Saloon by Kirsten Fullmer is a cross between romance, thriller and comedy. Matt Hopkins is looking for a new project to invest in. While settling into the quiet town of Sugar Mountain, Matt faced with the oddities of a small community. Everyone knows everyone’s business, yet no one observes the threats to Matt and Michelle. The Sugar Mountain Ladies Historical Society steps up to their meddlesome reputation to see if they can uncover the mysterious happenings.<br/> <br/>If you have read any</span>
  <span id="freeText15073937522419968594" style="display:none">Shadows in the Saloon by Kirsten Fullmer is a cross between romance, thriller and comedy. Matt Hopkins is looking for a new project to invest in. While settling into the quiet town of Sugar Mountain, Matt faced with the oddities of a small community. Everyone knows everyone’s business, yet no one observes the threats to Matt and Michelle. The Sugar Mountain Ladies Historical Society steps up to their meddlesome reputation to see if they can uncover the mysterious happenings.<br /> <br />If you have read any of Kirsten Fullmer’s novels you will know she has your stomach in knots one moment and laughing hilariously the next. Shadows in the Saloon does not disappoint. The plot takes you from one point to the next, but it is the ride that makes it so fun. Overall, I enjoyed this novel. The author brings her characters alive; you feel you have met them before; maybe she has met your neighbor, aunt, or beautician. You will definitely be entertained.  </span>
  <a data-text-id="15073937522419968594" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


