<span id="freeTextContainer18286277519059853222">I received a free copy of each book in this series in exchange for an honest review. I was not compensated for my opinion of these books.<br/><br/>As mentioned – did not read this series in order so I decided to just carry on with the trend and work backwards instead of forwards.<br/><br/>4 Reasons why this story deserved 4 stars:<br/><br/>Michelle. Once again Ms Fullmer spoils me with a strong female character that I cannot help but fall in love with. Very self sufficient. Very proud. Also very easy and quick to fall in lov</span>
  <span id="freeText18286277519059853222" style="display:none">I received a free copy of each book in this series in exchange for an honest review. I was not compensated for my opinion of these books.<br /><br />As mentioned – did not read this series in order so I decided to just carry on with the trend and work backwards instead of forwards.<br /><br />4 Reasons why this story deserved 4 stars:<br /><br />Michelle. Once again Ms Fullmer spoils me with a strong female character that I cannot help but fall in love with. Very self sufficient. Very proud. Also very easy and quick to fall in love. So what. It’s her prerogative.<br />Once again – a very fun and nice to read mystery. With some romance thrown in for good measure.<br />We have just enough paranormal / paranormal adjacent to give the story line a fun twist that makes it even more interesting to read.<br />Once again we’re up against our evil (OTT I know) villain The Mayor. I think he is a really interesting and fun bad guy. Never liked a bad guy before but there you go.</span>
