  <span id="freeText3429419611808156633" style="display:none">Michelle the hairdresser/salon owner seems to have a problem, or maybe more than one. She thinks maybe she has a ghost or a spirit warning her not to date Matt, the new man in town. But all the spooky things started a few hours before she first met Matt, so that couldn't be the problem. Could it? But Michelle's friends in the Sugar Mountain Ladies' Historical Society are on the job, trying to get to the bottom of it all and to make sure nothing bad happens to Michelle. And Matt? Even Judy, Michelle's mother, thinks he looks wonderful, and Judy is a notorious cougar. And, of course, Christmas is coming to Sugar Mountain, the most festive time of the year, and Michelle and Matt are all caught up in the conviviality. I really enjoyed reading this book. I got through it in just a few hours, I didn't get lost once, and I loved the ending. </span>
