        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/54775025-shadows-in-the-salon">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3632466557" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2567571724253950582"><strong>Not loving it.</strong><br/><br/>Grammar mistakes irritate me. <br/><br/>Waaay too much description. Sadly, I found myself doing what I always do with a book like this. I skipped to the next to the last chapter to see how it ended. <br/><br/>Premise was cute. If you aren’t a grammar freak, and you like detailed descriptions, it might be just the thing for you.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


